definitions.definition: First in importance , degree , or rank .
examples: Our prime concern here is to keep the community safe.

definitions.definition: First in time , order , or sequence .
examples: Both the English and French governments established prime meridians in their capitals.

definitions.definition: First in excellence , quality , or value .
examples: This is a prime location for a bookstore.

definitions.definition: Having exactly two integral factors: itself and unity (1 in the case of integers).
Such that if it divides a product , it divides one of the multiplicands .
Having its complement closed under multiplication .
Such that the annihilator of any nonzero submodule is equal to the annihilator of the whole module.
Marked or distinguished by the prime symbol.
Early; blooming; being in the first stage.
